<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="let-vt">let <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /let/    美 /let/  </p>
<p>(let, let)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[不用于被动语态] 让；允许：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He'd eat chocolate all day long if I let him.
我要是不拦着，他会整天不停地吃巧克力。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>let sb / sth do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Call me tomorrow and I'll let you know the lab result.
明天给我打电话，我会让你知道实验结果。</p><footer>2014 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We should not let this happen again. 
我们不能让这事再次发生。</p><footer>2009 福建</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>let sb / sth + adv / prep:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>let sb into the house
允许某人进屋</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please let me <strong>past</strong>.
请让我过去。</p></div>

<p>注: 在反义疑问句中，陈述部分以Let's开头的祈使句，疑问部分用shall we? 陈述部分以Let us / me开头的祈使句，疑问部分用will you?  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let's go out for a walk, shall we?
咱们出去散散步好吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let us enter, will you? 
你让我们进去，可以吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="2-bre">2.★ <strong>(BrE) 出租：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a house to let 
待出租的房屋</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="let-alone">let alone</h3>
<p>1.<strong>更不用说：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For most people, it's almost impossible to operate a computer without a mouse, let alone surf the Internet.
对大多数人来说，没有鼠标几乎无法操作计算机，更不用说上网了。</p><footer>2009 江苏书面表达</footer></div>

<h3 id="let-alone-be">let ... alone / be</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不要碰；不干涉：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let my things alone! 
别动我的东西。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let him alone / be. He needs a bit of freedom. 
别管他，他需要一点儿自由。</p></div>

<h3 id="let-down">let down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>使失望；辜负：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We did not want to let him down. 
我们不想让他失望。</p></div>

<h3 id="let-go-of-let-go">let go (of ...) / let ... go</h3>
<p>1.<strong>放开；释放；放手：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let go! You're hurting me!
放手！你弄疼我了！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's time to let the past go.
该忘掉过去了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When someone has deeply hurt you, it can be extremely difficult to let go of your hate.
当有人深深地伤害了你时，放下仇恨是非常困难的。</p><footer>2013 辽宁</footer></div>

<h3 id="let-in">let … in</h3>
<p>1.<strong>让…进来；放进：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The theatre was so small that they refused to let in any more people. 
剧院太小了，所以他们不让更多的人进来。</p><footer>北师大④ – 12</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I opened our bedroom windows to let in the wind. 
我打开了我们卧室的窗户通风。</p><footer>2009 福建改</footer></div>

<h3 id="let-off">let off</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>饶恕；放过：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was let off with a fine instead of being sent to prison.
没让她入狱，而是罚款了事。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>排放；放 (炮等)；使爆炸：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Many other human activities also let off carbon gases. 
许多其他的人类活动也排放含碳气体。</p><footer>译林⑤–2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Fireworks were being let off across the city, suddenly lighting up the night sky.
烟花在城市上空绽放，突然照亮了夜空。</p><footer>北师大新必修① – 3</footer></div>

<h3 id="let-off-steam">let off steam</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 发泄怒火；宣泄情绪</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="let-out">let out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>发出 (叫声等)；放出；泄露：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Throwing their hats into the air, the fans of the winning team let out loud shouts of victory.
获胜队的支持者把帽子抛向空中，发出胜利的欢呼声。</p><footer>2008 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It remains unknown who let out the secret. 
目前尚不清楚是谁泄露了秘密。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Let those in need <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (understand) that we will go all out to help them.   （2013 陕西改）  </li>
<li>He accidentally let <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ he had quarrelled with his wife and that he hadn't been home for a couple of weeks.  （2004 湖南改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. understand  2. out  </p></div>